cs.PL, cs.LG, cs.SE, cs.CL, cs.CC

Reasoning: 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages): The paper proposes a new module system for user-defined operators to implement an embedded domain specific language (EDSL) with good code-readability. It also discusses the extension of the host type system to support the proposed system. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): Although the paper does not directly discuss machine learning, the use of type systems and parsing methods may be relevant to the field of machine learning. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper proposes a new system for managing names and their scopes within an object-oriented language like Java. This may be relevant to software engineering practices. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper discusses the use of user-defined syntax extensions to implement an embedded domain specific language (EDSL). This may be relevant to the field of natural language processing. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity): The paper briefly discusses the time complexity of the parsing method used in the implementation of the proposed system. This may be relevant to the field of computational complexity.
